<!--
    Yoruba (Yorùbá) — yo
    Script : Latin with tonal diacritics (à á â è é ê ì í î ò ó ô ù ú û ṣ ẹ ọ ṃ ṇ);
             LTR.  Tonal diacritics are semantically essential — do NOT strip them.
    Approx.: ~47 M L1 speakers (Nigeria, Benin, Togo; diaspora).
    Register: Standard Modern Yoruba (Yorùbá Ìjọba) as used in broadcast media
              and education.
    Notes  : Yoruba is a tonal language; the three tones (high ´, mid no mark,
             low `) are written but are frequently omitted in casual digital text.
             These translations include full tonal marking for correctness.
             "Binge drinking" → mímu ọtí líle jù / mímu ọtí púpọ̀.
    Source : Translated from values-de/strings.xml (German source of truth).
-->
